# 5. まふゆをモデルに

Ena: Whew, I'm stuffed...
Akito: And you shoved all of your carrots onto my plate...
Mother: Don't forget that we have a guest, you two. Try to keep it down.
Mother: Again, Mafuyu, I'm very sorry about how heated things got between these two.
Mafuyu: No, it felt like a lively discussion since I'm an only child.
Ena: Yeah, I guess you don't have anyone to argue with as an only child. Why couldn't I have been one too?
Akito: That's my line.
Mother: Oh, actually... I'm not sure if we had the cleaners do the guest bedding. I think it's still sitting in the closet...
Ena: Oh, right. It's been forever since Airi last came over. The pillow's probably completely squished.
Mafuyu: That's okay, really. You don't have to mind me.
Ena: You must have nerves of steel if you don't care about sleeping on a flat pillow. That'd bother me way too much.
Mother: She's just being polite. But I appreciate your modesty, Mafuyu.
Mother: Also, the bath should be ready soon, so why don't you go first? In the meantime, we'll get your bed ready.
Mafuyu: Th-Thank you very much... But is it really okay for me to...?
Akito: Don't worry about us. I mean, you're one of the very few friends Ena has.
Akito: Also, it's best to go before Ena since it's always impossible to tell when she's going to be done.
Ena: I don't take that long! Quit giving her all these wrong ideas about me.
Mafuyu: Hehe. In that case, I'll go first.
Ena: Wait! The shampoo in the front's mine, so don't use it. The one in the back is Mom's so, use hers!
Akito: Why can't you just let her use yours...?
Ena: Because it's really expensive!
Mafuyu: Okay, the one in the back. Got it. I'll be right out.
Akito: Seriously, why's she friends with you...?
Ena: FYI, I'm usually the one taking care of her!
Akito: What? There's no way that's true.
Ena: Ugh... Akito's saying all this stuff without understanding what Mafuyu's actually like...
Ena: (To be fair, he probably wouldn't believe me if I told him about what's behind her honor student persona...)
Len: <H-Hello...? Ena?>
Ena: Oh, Len, hi. Sorry, I didn't realize you were still here.
Ena: Mafuyu's taking a bath right now. She should be out soon.
Len: <Okay... So, how's Mafuyu doing...?>
Ena: Hm? Hmm... I'm having a hard time telling as usual... So, no different from normal?
Len: <Okay... That's good to hear.>
Ena: Anyway... I need to come up with some ideas for my assignment before Mafuyu gets back...
Len: <What assignment...?>
Ena: For art class. It's been giving me a lot of trouble.
Len: <Art...?>
Len: <Can I see what you've drawn, Ena...?>
Len: <No, wait. I'm sorry... You need to work right now...>
Ena: I'm drawing a blank right now, so I don't mind if it's just for a bit.
Ena: Also, it's really nothing special... Oh, what if I showed you what I've drawn in my sketchbook?
Ena: Let's see... Here's a sketch of a flower vase. This one's of a wolf that I saw when I was little. And here's some stuff that I drew for N25.
Len: <Wow, so many drawings...! You're a really good artist, Ena.>
Ena: Huh? I'm nothing special, really...
Len: <I'd love to see more... Do you have any other drawings?>
Ena: Alright, then...
Ena: This is of one of my friends who's an idol now. She's really nice, super cute and has such a cheerful personality.
Ena: Oh, I have drawings of Kanade and the others too.
Len: <Oh, it's Miku..! She has such a gentle-looking smile on her face.>
Len: <Thank you for showing me these, Ena. They're all really good, but I think I liked the ones of everybody the most...>
Ena: Hehe. Thanks.
Ena: Oh, Len, want me to draw you?
Len: <Huh? M-Me...? I dunno... I think I'll get really jittery if you do...>
Len: <Wait, what about Mafuyu...?>
Ena: Huh? Mafuyu?
Len: <Y-Yeah. She's really calm and collected, so she'd be easier to draw compared to me, right...?>
Ena: I guess she wouldn't get nervous or jittery.
Ena: But Mafuyu? As a model...?
Mafuyu: Ena, I've finished taking my bath.
Mafuyu: ...? Is something wrong?
Ena: Hmm... Yeah, drawing you could be good practice.
Ena: Mafuyu, let me do a sketch of you.
Mafuyu: Me? Why...?
Len: <Oh, I asked her to. It's just... I want to see what Ena's drawing of you would look like.>
Mafuyu: Of me...?
Len: <Yeah. That is, unless you don't want to...>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: I don't mind...
Ena: Alright. Then, we'll get started after I take my bath.
Mafuyu: Okay...
